# Code Patterns for Full Stack Web Development

- Prefer reusable utils over inline logic. Extract when used twice.
- Before implementing any new tool or library, always search the web for latest documentation and github for best practices and implementation examples. 
- Result pattern: use safe/safeAsync for [data, null] | [null, Error]. Don't swallow errors. Don't use try/catch.
- In backend (API), Always throw `ApiError` over `Error`. Thrown errors are handled globally by `ErrorHandler`.
- Frontend catches errors globally as well using the `setupErrorListener` function. No need to handle errors locally.
- Middlewares: createMiddleware, c.set() for downstream. Providers: Context + useX, throw if used outside.
- Reuse existing: safeQuery, buildWhereActive, cn, zHexAddress, etc. Check lib/ before adding.
- Singleton for shared state (ErrorHandler). Factory for per-request (privy, logger).
- Types from source: Always try to infer types from source schemas (z.input) and existing types. Use omit or extend to extract relevant parts. Never duplicate if possible.
- One concerned domain per file: utils, hooks, providers separate. Try not to mix if it doesn't make sense.